    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The style and culture of the ancient Gallo-Germanic Belgæ tribes living from the 3rd century BCE onward in northern Gaul, between the English channel and the west bank of the Rhine. They were later found in Britain and Ireland.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
